# Linux Commands


## pwd
it refers to print working directory and it shows the directory which I am currently working at.

## ls
it stands for list and this command will list everything such as files and folders present in current directory.

## cd
it stands for change directory and it is used for navigation as using this we can navigate to any folder 
ex : cd name of folder : cd Downloads
cd takes us into the folder and to go back to previous directory we use : cd ..
To go to root directory we used : cd /

## cp
it stands for copy and it is used to copy files and paste the same file with different name in same folder.
it is used to create the copy of file in same folder.
Example:
cp file1.txt file2.txt

## rm
it stands for remove and it is used to remove or delete the file from current folder.
To remove any file from folder : rm name of file which we want to remove.
Example:
rm filename.txt


## mkdir
it stands for make directory and it is used to create new directory.

## rmdir 
it stands for remove directory and it is used to remove folder which has no files inside it.
to remove folder which have files in it we use : rm -r name of folder

## touch
It is used to create an empty file.
Example:
touch file1.txt

## cat
It is used to see what's inside the file
Example:
cat file1.txt



